cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.SE

The paper discusses potential steganographic methods that may be applied to SCTP and may pose a threat to network security. This falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and network security (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of new SCTP features like multi-homing and multistreaming, which may fall under the categories of information theory (cs.IT) and multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper suggests countermeasures that may be used to mitigate the identified threats, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE).
